{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c69fa313-eaf6-4edc-86df-3fc046c70c3e","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, make these two changes:\n\n**1. Remove (or set to `false`) the VSTest property:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\n**2. That's it.** `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0` already defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not explicitly enabled.\n\n### What changes in practice\n\n| | VSTest (`dotnet test`) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console` host | Test app is its own host |\n| CLI | `dotnet test` still works | Can also run the test exe directly |\n| Output | `.trx` via `/logger:trx` | `--report-trx` flag |\n\n### Quick checklist\n\n- **Remove** `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` from your `.csproj` / `Directory.Build.props`.\n- **Verify** with `dotnet test` — it should still work.\n- If you run tests directly (e.g., `./MyTests.exe`), use `--help` to see the new CLI options.\n- If you use `.runsettings`, review compatibility — most settings carry over, but some logger/adapter configs may need updating.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c87e573-9634-45fe-9e97-fd9c782c2630","outputTokens":318,"requestId":"E3DA:8E236:160E7BC:18AC244:6A052008"},"id":"f55f6980-a3f9-489f-b1b3-0079de5f67ce","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:06:25.731Z","parentId":"8ec2630c-93f7-4e74-9968-e98bd24553c3"}
